==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Theta
<hw>The"ta</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., fr. Gr.
<grk>qh^ta</grk>, the Greek letter ⟦theta⟧, ⟦THETA⟧.]</ety> <def>A
letter of the Greek alphabet corresponding to <it>th</it> in English; --
sometimes called the <xex>unlucky</xex> letter, from being used by the
judges on their ballots in passing condemnation on a prisoner, it being
the first letter of the Greek <grk>qa`natos</grk>, death.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Theta function</b></col> <fld>(Math.)</fld>, <cd>one of a
group of functions used in developing the properties of elliptic
functions.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Thetical</ent>⟦br⟧
